nsors </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Horror based around building dread and paranoia</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > A short experience intended to be finished in under 2 hours</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/7e97ca1481822493ba3a78343a894902.poster.avif?t=1730391162\" width=590 height=358 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/7e97ca1481822493ba3a78343a894902.webm?t=1730391162\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/7e97ca1481822493ba3a78343a894902.mp4?t=1730391162\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >The Story</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Years ago, sensors discovered quite the anomaly. A swirling mass of liquid hydrogen surrounds a supermassive black hole. Heat and EM readings indicated the body were off the charts. You are manning the U.N.S. Icarus, a scout ship hosted by the carrier, U.N.S. Daedalus. Localized interference patterns were causing scanners and probes to malfunction so... the task falls to you. Deploy sensors, scan the area, and get back to the Daedalus.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/31f57d133da283961f92a91546aa67e9.poster.avif?t=1730391162\" width=590 height=188 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/31f57d133da283961f92a91546aa67e9.webm?t=1730391162\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2476040/extras/31f57d133da283